# 🧠 Decision Boundary Visualization using ANN

## 📌 Overview

Built a neural network classifier to visualize how decision boundaries are formed in feature space.

✔ Multiclass classification (Iris dataset)  
✔ Visualized nonlinear decision regions  
✔ Demonstrated model interpretability  

---

## 📂 Dataset

- Dataset: Iris Dataset (sklearn built-in)
- Source: sklearn.datasets.load_iris()
- Samples: 150
- Features Used: 2 (for visualization)

### Classes:

Setosa  
Versicolor  
Virginica  

---

## ⚙️ Approach

### 1. Data Preprocessing

- Selected 2 features for visualization  
- Applied StandardScaler  
- Train-test split  

### 2. Model Architecture

Input Layer (2 features)  
Dense (16) + ReLU  
Dense (16) + ReLU  
Output Layer (3 neurons, Softmax)

### 3. Visualization

- Created mesh grid  
- Predicted class on grid  
- Plotted contour regions  

---

## 📊 Results

- High classification accuracy  
- Clear nonlinear decision boundaries  

---

## 🧠 Key Insights

- ANN captures nonlinear relationships  
- Visualization improves interpretability  

---

## 🚀 How to Run

pip install tensorflow numpy matplotlib scikit-learn  

python decision_boundary.py  

